to change the password---->
sudo passwd "username"


<-------------------GIT------------------>

1. if error comes like - "Fix “Unable to lock the administration directory (/var/lib/dpkg/)” in Ubuntu"
Solution - first need to remove this directory
do it as following--->
sudo rm /var/lib/dpkg/lock

then reconfigure this directory--->
sudo dpkg --configure -a

2.Install git-->
sudo apt-get install git

3. configure your account(username, email from git) to local machine--->
git config--global user.name "username"
git config--global user.email "email"

4. make a dir for git to keep it synced with the git repository
mkdir

ALL INSIDE the dir made in step 4

5.to add a readme file write
echo "# dir-name" >> README.md

6.now initialise the git dir(not required if I have cloned a existing repository)
git init


7.to add a file to the git
git add "file-name"


8.now we can add a comment to this file
git commit -m "comment"

9.now to add this file, commit to the remote directory
git remote add origin https://github.com/shadyStan1/taikhana2


10.now to push the changes to the remote directory
git push -u origin master



---------------------CLONING------------
11.git clone https://...........



--------------------Get Status----------
12.git status



----------------to reset all the changes----------
13.git reset --hard




-------------to check configured details---------
14.git config --list
